{
  "mcpServers": {
    "filesystem-bridge": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["./dist/filesystem-bridge/server.js"],
      "env": {
        "ALLOWED_PATHS": "/Users/yourname/projects,/Users/yourname/Documents",
        "READ_ONLY": "false",
        "MAX_FILE_SIZE": "10485760"
      }
    },
    "shell-bridge": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["./dist/shell-bridge/server.js"],
      "env": {
        "TIMEOUT": "120000",
        "ALLOWED_COMMANDS": "ls,pwd,cd,cat,grep,find,git,npm,node,python",
        "BLOCKED_COMMANDS": "rm,rmdir,del,format,fdisk,sudo"
      }
    }
  }
}

/*
Claude Desktop MCP Configuration Guide:

1. Find your Claude Desktop config directory:
   - macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
   - Windows: %APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json
   - Linux: ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json

2. Edit the config file and add the mcpServers section above

3. Adjust the ALLOWED_PATHS to your project directories

4. Restart Claude Desktop

5. The new tools should appear in your conversation:
   - read_file
   - write_file
   - edit_file
   - glob_search
   - run_command
   - run_background
   - get_current_directory
   - change_directory

Security Notes:
- ALLOWED_PATHS: Comma-separated list of directories the filesystem bridge can access
- READ_ONLY: Set to "true" to disable write operations
- ALLOWED_COMMANDS: Whitelist specific commands (optional, comment out for more freedom)
- BLOCKED_COMMANDS: Always block dangerous commands like rm, format, etc.
*/